  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First, I have to say that there was-- before-- right before Purim, there was a committee-- a committee organized in the kehilla that would collect money, which was called for [YIDDISH] which means collect money for flour to bake the matzo for people that are-- that are poor and couldn't-- couldn't afford it.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would-- they would select a person that would-- I don't know exactly-- they-- I believe that they would have to travel to the city of Khust to get that flour.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that flour had to be specially-- specially guarded, that-- that there wouldn't be any moisture in it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and this was always done by, I remember, a-- a-- a poor Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and for that-- for that work, he was-- he was getting-- getting his share of flour.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they would bring that and store it into an area where they had in the-- in the-- in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And just before-- right after Purim, they would start-- start get-together groups-- four or five families-- and they would-- they would bake it, bake the-- the matzos.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Shabbat-- Shabbat was-- was a-- a-- a totally-- totally-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] how should I say that-- it was a very, very restful time, because it was observed very strictly.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it is-- it is in-- in Jewish folklore, known as the [YIDDISH] Shabbat, that you got the-- you are getting a additional soul on Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Shabbos was very restful and-- and-- and-- and spiritual.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- the money-- there wasn't one that-- person, that-- unless he was very ill, that wouldn't-- wouldn't participate in the services.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As I-- I said, this was a-- a Hasidic type of-- of community.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
